<inglise> Whereas the individual Directives already adopted in the field of safety and health at work apply, unless otherwise specified, to sea fishing; whereas, therefore, it may in some cases be necessary to specify the particular characteristics of this activity in order to ensure that the individual Directives are applied in the best way; </inglise>
<eesti> t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja -ohutuse valdkonnas juba vastuv&otilde;etud &uuml;ksikdirektiive kohaldatakse ka merekalap&uuml;&uuml;gi suhtes, kui ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti; seet&otilde;ttu v&otilde;ib teatavatel juhtudel osutuda vajalikuks t&auml;psustada k&otilde;nealuse tegevuse olemust, et tagada &uuml;ksikdirektiivide optimaalne kohaldamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council Directive 92/29/EEC of 31 March 1992 on the minimum safety and health requirements for improved medical treatment on board vessels(6) is applicable in full to the sea fishing industry; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 31. m&auml;rtsi 1992. aasta direktiivi 92/29/EM&Uuml; (ohutuse ja tervishoiu miinimumn&otilde;uete kohta, et osutada paremaid raviteenuseid laevadel) (6) kohaldatakse merekalap&uuml;&uuml;gi suhtes t&auml;ielikult; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Directive constitutes concrete progress towards the achievement of the social dimension of the internal market, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev direktiiv on konkreetne samm siseturu sotsiaalse ulatuse v&auml;ljaarendamisel, </eesti>
